    "body": "<p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>Anurag\u2019s girlfriend loves playing with squares. On Valentine\u2019s Day, she requested him to arrange some squares of unit area in a special way. She asked him to arrange all the squares such that the perimeter is minimum. Your task is to help Anurag and tell the minimum possible perimeter to his girlfriend. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The only line of input contains <b>N</b>, the number of squares of unit area. </p>\n\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Print the minimum possible perimeter for <b>N</b> squares. </p>\n\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>6</sup></b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n6\n</pre>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1: </b>If 2 squares of unit area are placed next to each other, the perimeter would be 6.</p>",
